---
import SectionHeading from "./SectionHeading.astro";

const loop = [
  {
    n: "01",
    title: "An escape slips through",
    body: "A change merges that a reviewer should have caught. Inevitable, especially early. It's also your most valuable signal.",
  },
  {
    n: "02",
    title: "Triage which reviewer missed",
    body: "Find the concern that wasn't covered, or the reviewer whose prompt was too loose to catch it.",
  },
  {
    n: "03",
    title: "Adjust the policy",
    body: "Tighten a prompt, add a narrow reviewer, or harden a trigger. It's a diff against reviewers.yaml, reviewed like any other.",
  },
  {
    n: "04",
    title: "The gate gets sharper",
    body: "The next changeset meets a better policy. Convergence over time beats strict perfection up front.",
  },
];
---

<section class="section govern" id="govern">
  <div class="container">
    <SectionHeading title="You govern the policy.">
      Bastion doesn't take the human out of the loop, it moves them up a level:
      from reviewing every diff to authoring, curating, and governing the
      reviewers that do. Your interface becomes the registry and the escape
      feed.
    </SectionHeading>

    <div class="govern-grid">
      <div class="govern-left" data-reveal>
        <div class="codeowner-card">
          <div class="codeowner-head">
            <span class="codeowner-file">.github/CODEOWNERS</span>
            <span class="pill pill--neutral"><span class="pill-dot"></span>human review required</span>
          </div>
          <pre class="codeowner-body"><code><span class="t-com"># Changing the review policy is itself reviewed.</span>
<span class="t-glob">bastion/reviewers.yaml</span>   <span class="t-key">@your-org/platform</span></code></pre>
        </div>
        <p class="govern-note">
          Because reviewers are declarative and static, any PR that weakens the
          gate, loosens a prompt, drops a trigger, or downgrades a gate to an
          advisor shows up as a diff a human must approve. The policy can't
          quietly erode.
        </p>
        <ul class="govern-points">
          <li>Reviewers are the agents you already trust, written down.</li>
          <li>Even earnest agents can game a check; governance makes it visible.</li>
          <li>The registry is the artifact. Review it, version it, own it.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <ol class="loop" data-reveal style="--reveal-delay:90ms" aria-label="The escape to improvement loop">
        {
          loop.map((s, i) => (
            <li class="loop-step" style={`--i:${i}`}>
              <span class="loop-n">{s.n}</span>
              <div class="loop-body">
                <h3>{s.title}</h3>
                <p>{s.body}</p>
              </div>
            </li>
          ))
        }
      </ol>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .govern-grid {
    margin-top: clamp(2rem, 1rem + 3vw, 3rem);
    display: grid;
    gap: clamp(1.75rem, 1rem + 3vw, 3rem);
    align-items: start;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1fr);
  }
  @media (min-width: 920px) {
    .govern-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    }
  }

  .codeowner-card {
    border: 1px solid var(--line-strong);
    border-radius: var(--radius-3);
    overflow: hidden;
    background: var(--paper-raised);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-1);
  }
  .codeowner-head {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    padding: 0.65rem 0.9rem;
    background: var(--paper-2);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
  }
  .codeowner-file {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--ink);
  }
  .codeowner-body {
    padding: 1rem;
    overflow-x: auto;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }
  .codeowner-body .t-com {
    color: var(--tok-com);
    font-style: italic;
  }
  .codeowner-body .t-glob {
    color: var(--steel);
  }
  .codeowner-body .t-key {
    color: var(--tok-key);
    font-weight: 560;
  }

  .govern-note {
    margin-top: 1.4rem;
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    color: var(--ink-2);
  }
  .govern-points {
    margin-top: 1.2rem;
    list-style: none;
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.7rem;
  }
  .govern-points li {
    position: relative;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--ink-2);
  }
  .govern-points li::before {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 0.5em;
    width: 0.55rem;
    height: 0.55rem;
    border: 1.5px solid var(--steel);
    border-radius: 2px;
    rotate: 45deg;
  }

  /* the loop */
  .loop {
    list-style: none;
    position: relative;
    display: grid;
    gap: 0;
    padding-left: 0.5rem;
  }
  .loop-step {
    position: relative;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 3rem 1fr;
    gap: 1rem;
    padding-block: 1.1rem;
  }
  .loop-step + .loop-step {
    border-top: 1px dashed var(--line);
  }
  .loop-n {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--steel);
    padding-top: 0.15rem;
  }
  .loop-body h3 {
    font-size: var(--text-md);
    margin-bottom: 0.3rem;
  }
  .loop-body p {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--ink-2);
  }
  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: no-preference) {
    .js .loop.is-in .loop-step {
      animation: loop-in var(--dur-2) var(--ease-out) backwards;
      animation-delay: calc(var(--i) * 90ms + 100ms);
    }
    @keyframes loop-in {
      from {
        opacity: 0;
        transform: translateY(8px);
      }
    }
  }
</style>
